Model Fit

df_values <- c(5, 7, 9, 11)
overall <- NULL
for(df in df_values){
  overall <- smooth.spline(train$full_sq, train$price_doc, df=df) %>%
    broom::augment() %>%
    mutate(df=df) %>%
    bind_rows(overall)
}
overall <- overall %>% 
  as_tibble()
multiple_df <- overall %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=x)) +
  geom_point(aes(y=y), size=1) +
  geom_line(aes(y=.fitted), col="blue", size=1) +
  facet_wrap(~df, nrow=2) +
  labs(title="Splines fit w/ different degrees of freedom")
multiple_df

Something like df=9 seems to work the best

Create Submission File

mod <- smooth.spline(train$full_sq, train$price_doc, df=9)
test2 <- predict(mod, test$full_sq)
submission <- data.frame(test$id, test2$y)
names(submission) <- c("id", "price_doc")
write.csv(submission, "submission.csv", row.names=FALSE)
